Bind Content and Presentation
----field----
field: {00E1D306-96BD-4B32-85B4-CD63C53CC6C1}
name: Abstract
key: abstract
content-length: 183

<p>A quick review of binding content and presentation for the "Build My First Site" exercise. We'll show how to bind layout's and sublayout's to our Data Template Standard Values.</p>
----field----
field: {5A5684BB-8B54-44F6-ABCC-2BADA05ADA5D}
name: Body
key: body
content-length: 3141

<h3>Discussion</h3>
<p>Our last step in building our First Site is to bind our presentation elements to the data items. </p>
<p>To bind presentation elements to the data, we will go to each of our data template's standard values and tell Sitecore which layout and sublayout to use for each of our content types (the Home Page and Products). </p>
<p>The Home Page should use the following presentation elements: </p>
<ul>
  <li>Main Layout</li>
  <li>Generic Display Sublayout </li>
</ul>
<p>The Product pages should use the following presentation elements: </p>
<ul>
  <li>Main Layout </li>
  <li>Product Display Sublayout </li>
</ul>
<p>Note that both the Home Page and the Product pages use the same layout. The only change is which presentation element is put into the "myfirstsite-content" placeholder. </p>
<h3>Activity</h3>
<p>Open the Template Manager (<strong>Sitecore &gt; Template Manager</strong>) and navigate to the Home Page template. In the upper right, click on selecting Builder-Options, then click on the "Standard Values" button to be taken to the template's standard values. Remember that data template standard values are where you can set default settings for content items which are based on that data template. </p>
<p>Before binding the presentation settings for the home item, make sure you have selected the "__Standard Values" node under the Home Page template. Then, on the Presentation tab, click "Details": </p>
<p><img alt="" width="500" src="~/media/91D580D2DDE64DDFA1B5D8E7442D18BF.ashx" /></p>
<p>Then click "Edit" by the Default device. </p>
<p><img alt="" width="500" src="~/media/EECA64816EF348839A4903CEBE6A4DCF.ashx" /></p>
<p>For the layout, in the drop-down menu, select the Main Layout. </p>
<p><img alt="" width="485" height="633" src="~/media/E18B83483686440CA5D52DBAF625FB70.ashx" /> </p>
<p>To assign the Generic Display sublayout to the "myfirstsite content" placeholder, click "Controls," then "Add"and browse to select the Generic Display sublayout from the Sublayout folder. In the Placeholder field, type "myfirstsite content". </p>
<p><img alt="" width="487" height="633" src="~/media/66A93E690CD14DD3B0558DA3DE57AE7E.ashx" /></p>
<p>After clicking "OK," your screen should look like this: </p>
<p><img alt="" width="484" height="631" src="~/media/CA6A507303CD45299A474481D658AAE8.ashx" /></p>
<p>This indicates that Sitecore will place the Generic Display sublayout into the "myfirstsite content" placeholder on the Main Layout. </p>
<p>Click "OK" and "OK" again to save your changes. </p>
<p>Repeat the steps above for the Product template, however this time placing the Product Display rendering from the Renderings folder into the "myfirstsite content" placeholder. When you are done, your control settings for the Product template's standard values should look like this: </p>
<p><img alt="" width="487" height="631" src="~/media/05E0DF8E31B641EA992E8AF7CDEC9EAF.ashx" /></p>
<p>Note: be sure to have selected the Product template's standard values, which you can find through Builder-Options, and not the Product data template itself prior to binding the presentation elements. </p>
